  "market_context": "Crude oil futures rallied on the monthly chart into a buyside liquidity pool near 91.00, with old monthly highs and buy stops resting above. After the raid of those buy stops, the analyst drops to the daily chart to observe how order flow transitions from bullish to bearish.",
  "key_observation": "Three distinct bearish order flow signals fire in sequence at different times: first the bullish FVG inversion, then the change in state of delivery (closure below up-close candles forming an order block), and finally—much later—the market structure shift below the swing low.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify on the monthly chart the old high and resting buy stops near 91.00 as the buyside liquidity draw.",
    "Note the raid of those buy stops and the old monthly high, signaling the potential top.",
    "Drop to the daily chart and define the three ways order flow can shift bearish: inversion of the bullish FVG, change in state of delivery via closure below the up-close candle series, or a market structure shift below the swing low.",
    "Observe the first displacement candle closing through more than 50% of the bullish FVG but not fully below it — treat as a partial inversion; prefer waiting for a full closure below.",
    "Confirm the full closure below the FVG, which simultaneously delivers the inversion and the change in state of delivery, validating the up-close candles as a bearish order block.",
    "Watch the next candle retest the new order block without yet shifting structure, forming an additional up-close candle.",
    "One to two days later, price expands lower and finally breaks the swing low, producing the delayed market structure shift.",
    "Zoom out and note that on the MSS, price retraces into a premium order block, reacts, forms a secondary order block on the retest, and continues lower."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Inversion and change in state of delivery typically signal earlier than a market structure shift, allowing entries before the expansion; MSS entries require a retracement into a premium PD array. Choosing between inversions, MSS, or order blocks depends on what fits the trader's system.",
